FastPattern.description: ServiceWarning: Could not find IPv6 gateway

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) ([^:]+): Blade in bay (\d+) has been powered (\S+)

FastField.defaultValue: Blade in bay $4 has been powered $5
Blade in bay $4 has been powered $5

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: Momentary Press virtual command enacted on blade
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ .+?Momentary Press virtual command enacted on blade

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: php; creating rrd update script
ServiceInfo: php; Removing static route for monitor
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ php: [^:]+: Removing static route for monitor [\d.]+ and adding a new route through [\d.]+

FastPattern.description: IPTrafficAudit: php; pfSense package system has detected an ip change
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ php: [^:]+: pfSense package system has detected an ip change [\d.]* -\> *[\d.]+

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: php; on IP address; interface

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ php: [^:]+: Successful login for user '[^']+' from: [-\w.]+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ php: [^:]+: webConfigurator authentication error for '[^']+' from [-\w.]+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ snort\[\d+\]: \[[\d:]+\] \(ssp_ssl\) Invalid Client HELLO after Server HELLO Detected
^\d+ [-\w.]+.+?\S+ logged into the Onboard Administrator from [\d.]+

FastPattern.description: ServiceWarning: failed to resolve retry again
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+.+?failed to resolve host \S+ will retry later again

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: filterdns; IP address already present
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ filterdns:\s*IP address [-\w.]+ already present on table \S+

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: OA; {DNS Server, SNMP Trap Destination} pingable
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ OA: The (?:DNS Server|SNMP Trap Destination) '[^']+' is pingable

FastPattern.description: ServiceWarning: pfSctl; could not finish read
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ pfSctl: could not finish read in a reasonable time

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: {Stopping all packages, List of packages to reinstall}
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ [^:]+: [^:]+: (?:Stopping all packages|List of packages to reinstall)

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: {Finished reinstalling, Attempting to reinstall, Finished installing}
ServiceInfo: {Uninstalling package, Finished uninstalling, Reinstalling package}
ServiceInfo: radvd, {no auto-selected prefix, attempting to reread, resuming normal operation, Exiting, sigterm received, sending stop adverts, gettimeofday}
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ radvd\[\d+\]: (?:no auto-selected prefix on interface \w+|attempting to reread config file|resuming normal operation|Exiting, sigterm or sigint received|sending stop adverts|gettimeofday\(\) went backwards|removing [/\w.]+)

FastPattern.description: ServiceWarning: radvd, no buffer space available
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ radvd\[\d+\]: sendmsg: No buffer space available
^\d+ [-\w.]+ pf:.*?block in on \w+: \([\w ]+, next-header UDP \(17\) payload length: \d+\)

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: pf, TCP, UDP, IGMP, ICMP packet info
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ pf:.*?(?:block in on \w+:)?\s*\(tos \w+,.*?ttl \d+, id \d+, offset \d+, flags \[\w+\], proto (?:TCP|UDP|IGMP|ICMP)? \(\d+\), length \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ pf:\s*?[\d.]+\.\d+ > [\d.]+\.\d+: ICMP echo request, id \d+, seq \d+, length \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ dhcpd: Wrote \d+ (?:(?:deleted|new dynamic) host decls|leases)? to leases file

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: php; tunnel endpoints has changed
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ php: [^:]+: [^:]+: One or more \w+ tunnel endpoints (?:has|may have)? changed its IP

FastPattern.description: ICMPTrafficAudit: pf, ICMP net unreachable, ICMP udp port unreachable, ICMP time-exceeded, ICMP host unreachable
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ pf:\s*?[\d.]+\.\d+ > [\d.]+\.\d+: (?:ICMP net [\d.]+ unreachable,|ICMP [\d.]+ udp port \d+ unreachable,|ICMP time exceeded in-transit|ICMP host [\d.]+ unreachable)

FastPattern.description: ServiceInfo: pf, Domain, SIP, Refused, NXDomain
ServiceInfo: pf, OPTIONS sip, Via: SIP, Content-Length
ServiceInfo: root: is beginning|ending the update cycle.
